node.text:
If you didn't know.
.
If you're new to me and Pro Wrestling.
.
This is who I roll with. These are the types of people that brought me in the biz. These are who specifically picked me to stand with them.
.
People like Sayama (Tiger Mask) who has taken me aside to have deep discussions on Martial Arts and Wrestling.
.
Fujinami (Who watched me roll in the NJPW ring my first trip to wrestle and told me it reminded him of watching Gotch)
.
Inoki - who has been one of mentors and teachers in Professional Wrestling.
.
All of us sharing a lineage to Karl Gotch.
.
It ain't part time. It never has been.
.
It ain't a "hobby". It never was.

node.text:
A big Congratulations to @pathsmith as he win the @usawrestling world team trials in Greco this weekend.
.
Pat did some of his camp with me, @bigtonynelson, @victorhenrymma and others up in Lake Arrowhead and his hard work has paid off well. Here's a little video of us drilling up there. 
.
Nice work Pat!
.
#Wrestling

I will have three new Catch Wrestling technique videos coming out soon from @bjj.fanatics. Here I get to sit down with @bernardofariabjj and show you guys some of what we filmed.
.
Enjoy!
.

node.text:
#tbt to winning the King of Pancrase title representing NJPW with my brothers Iizuka and Nakanishi in my corner. Enson Inoue was there with us too.
.
For me, I felt a lot pride to raise the flag of New Japan Pro Wrestling and for Pro Wrestling at large. Working and shooting - two sides of the same coin.
.
.
.
.
.
.
